'''{{Path|/usr/portage/profiles/package.mask}}''' is [[Article description::a file containing package atoms to mask.]] This file is controlled by developers of the main ebuild repository (gentoo.git).

After syncing, end users can take a look in {{Path|/etc/portage/package.mask}} for some up-to-date examples on packages that are currently masked in the Gentoo ebuild repository. The comments preceding the package will provide insight into why the package has been masked.

== Format ==

* Comment lines begin with <code>#</code> (no inline comments).
* One <var>DEPEND</var> atom per line.

== Examples ==

{{FileBox|filename=/usr/portage/package.mask|title=package.mask example|1=
# mask out versions 1.0.4496 of the nvidia
# drivers and later
>=media-video/nvidia-kernel-1.0.4496
>=media-video/nvidia-glx-1.0.4496
}}

